# InvestiKid

A children's finance-education app (web + iOS), heading to a TestFlight beta.

## Layout
- `backend/` ‚Äî FastAPI + SQLAlchemy 2.0 (async) + Alembic + Postgres. Deployed on **Railway**.
- `frontend/` ‚Äî React 18 + Vite + TypeScript + TanStack Query + Tailwind + shadcn/ui, with a **Capacitor iOS** app in `frontend/ios/`. Web deployed on **Vercel**.
- `docs/superpowers/specs/` and `docs/superpowers/plans/` ‚Äî dated design specs and implementation plans. Read the relevant spec/plan before changing a feature.

## Golden rules
- **Never read or modify any `.env` file.** Secrets live there; `.env.example` lists the variables.
- Commit to `main`. End commit messages with the project trailer: `Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>` (match existing style).
- **Railway deploys the backend only when CI is green** (5 jobs: frontend, backend, security, a11y, responsive). Don't treat a backend change as deployed until CI passes. Vercel auto-deploys the frontend from `main`.
- Follow **TDD**: write the failing test first, then the minimal code to pass. Keep changes small and focused; touch only what the task needs.
- DB schema changes require a **hand-written, chained Alembic migration** (set `down_revision` to the current head ‚Äî check `alembic heads` first). No blind autogenerate.
- After frontend changes that must reach the iOS app, run `npm run build && npx cap sync ios`; native changes then need an Xcode rebuild.
- **Beta:** commit straight to `main` (skip `testing`/`staging`) until official release. **Ask before any production DB migration** whether to snapshot first. Manual Vercel prod deploy = `vercel deploy --prod --archive=tgz --yes` then `vercel alias set <slug> app.investikid.ai` (the `--prod` deploy does NOT auto-switch the alias). New `/internal/*` cron POSTs need a CSRF allowlist entry (`backend/app/core/csrf.py`).
- After every push to `main`, update the progress trackers (`docs/MASTER-BACKLOG.md`, `docs/superpowers/PROGRESS.md`) in the same task.

## Domain invariants (settled ‚Äî match unless the user changes them)
- **Web auth is same-site.** Prod web (`app.investikid.ai`) calls the API at **`https://api.investikid.ai`**, never `investikid.up.railway.app` ‚Äî same registrable domain keeps the `SameSite=None` auth cookie first-party (the railway host is cross-site ‚Üí Safari/Chrome block it ‚Üí "Could not start your session"). Keep Vercel Production `VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.investikid.ai`. Spec: `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-15-web-auth-same-site-api-design.md`.
- **Content generation criteria.** Write in the market's English variant (**American for US/CA** ‚Äî mom/neighbor/color; British elsewhere; `_market_english`). Ground examples in the verified `MarketBrief` (no UK products in non-GB markets). Keep lessons diverse (rotate names/scenarios, blend card/quiz/scenario, sibling-`avoid` list) and spread concepts across distinct facets per level (no 3+-concept single-product stacking). Tiered depth = 10/15/20 lessons for tier 1/2/3.
- **Simulator apply-missions.** `evaluate_apply_missions` reads global portfolio state, so it MUST be scoped to the child's `active_market_code`, else one action multiplies rewards across markets. Keep missions sparse/curated (no bulk same-type). Investing modules auto-attach one mission to their culminating lesson (`investing_missions.py`: growth‚Üí`first_buy`, risk‚Üí`diversify` n=3; 20 XP + admin-editable per-market cash).

